cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for autonomous driving. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks for affordance learning, which falls under the category of machine learning. Hence, cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely category. The paper also discusses the use of Open Street Map road vector attributes, which falls under the category of natural language processing and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a possible category. The paper also discusses the use of real-time sensors, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence. Hence, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the experimental evaluation of the proposed method, which falls under the category of machine learning and statistics. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a possible category.
